      "citation_id": "[CITATION_4]",
      "span_text": "Metronidazole clearance has been recently proposed as a highly sensitive method for evaluating liver function [CITATION_3] . This method consists of measuring plasma hydroxy-metronidazole/metronidazole ratio by high-performance liquid chromatography (HPLC) following the intravenous administration of a single dose of metronidazole. The test has been used to show that anti-HCV-positive blood donors and chronic hepatitis C patients have a decreased capacity to metabolize metronidazole compared to healthy individuals, thus demonstrating its usefulness for detecting impaired liver function in HCV-infected individuals, even in the absence of liver cirrhosis [CITATION_4] ."
